BoundAttributes.Name: TextUpdateSuppression
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            When TextUpdateSuppression is true (which is default) the text can not be updated by bindings while the component is focused in BSS (not WASM).
            This solves issue #1012: Textfield swallowing chars when typing rapidly
            If you need to update the input's text while it is focused you can set this parameter to false.
            Note: on WASM text update suppression is not active, so this parameter has no effect.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Validation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A validation func or a validation attribute. Supported types are:
            <para>Func<T, bool> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false</para>
            <para>Func<T, string> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null </para>
            <para>Func<T, IEnumerable< string >> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<object, string, IEnumerable< string >> input Form.Model, Full Path of Member ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task< bool >> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task< string >> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task<IEnumerable< string >>> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<object, string, Task<IEnumerable< string >>> input Form.Model, Full Path of Member ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations.ValidationAttribute instances</para>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Validation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A validation func or a validation attribute. Supported types are:
            <para>Func<T, bool> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false</para>
            <para>Func<T, string> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null </para>
            <para>Func<T, IEnumerable< string >> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<object, string, IEnumerable< string >> input Form.Model, Full Path of Member ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task< bool >> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task< string >> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task<IEnumerable< string >>> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<object, string, Task<IEnumerable< string >>> input Form.Model, Full Path of Member ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations.ValidationAttribute instances</para>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Validation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A validation func or a validation attribute. Supported types are:
            <para>Func<T, bool> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false</para>
            <para>Func<T, string> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null </para>
            <para>Func<T, IEnumerable< string >> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<object, string, IEnumerable< string >> input Form.Model, Full Path of Member ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task< bool >> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task< string >> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task<IEnumerable< string >>> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<object, string, Task<IEnumerable< string >>> input Form.Model, Full Path of Member ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations.ValidationAttribute instances</para>
            </summary>

<summary>
            A validation func or a validation attribute. Supported types are:
            <para>Func<T, bool> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false</para>
            <para>Func<T, string> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null </para>
            <para>Func<T, IEnumerable< string >> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<object, string, IEnumerable< string >> input Form.Model, Full Path of Member ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task< bool >> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task< string >> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task<IEnumerable< string >>> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<object, string, Task<IEnumerable< string >>> input Form.Model, Full Path of Member ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations.ValidationAttribute instances</para>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedItemChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Callback is called when a row has been clicked and returns the selected item.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedItemsChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Callback is called whenever items are selected or deselected in multi selection mode.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RowClick
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Callback is called whenever a row is clicked.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: StartedEditingItem
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Callback is called when an item has begun to be edited. Returns the item being edited.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CancelledEditingItem
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Callback is called when the process of editing an item has been cancelled. Returns the item which was previously in edit mode.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CommittedItemChanges
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Callback is called when the changes to an item are committed. Returns the item whose changes were committed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SortMode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Controls whether data in the DataGrid can be sorted. This is overridable by each column.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Filterable
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Controls whether data in the DataGrid can be filtered. This is overridable by each column.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Hideable
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Controls whether columns in the DataGrid can be hidden. This is overridable by each column.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowColumnOptions
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Controls whether to hide or show the column options. This is overridable by each column.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Breakpoint
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            At what breakpoint the table should switch to mobile layout. Takes None, Xs, Sm, Md, Lg and Xl the default behavior is breaking on Xs.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Elevation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The higher the number, the heavier the drop-shadow. 0 for no shadow.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Square
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Set true to disable rounded corners
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Outlined
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If true, table will be outlined.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Bordered
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If true, table's cells will have left/right borders.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ColGroup
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a group of one or more columns in a table for formatting.
            Ex:
            table
                colgroup
                   col span="2" style="background-color:red"
                   col style="background-color:yellow"
                 colgroup
                 header
                 body
            table
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Dense
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Set true for rows with a narrow height
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Hover
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Set true to see rows hover on mouse-over.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Striped
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If true, striped table rows will be used.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FixedHeader
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            When true, the header will stay in place when the table is scrolled. Note: set Height to make the table scrollable.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FixedFooter
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            When true, the footer will be visible is not scrolled to the bottom. Note: set Height to make the table scrollable.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FilterDefinitions
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The list of FilterDefinitions that have been added to the data grid. FilterDefinitions are managed by the data
            grid automatically when using the built in filter UI. You can also programmatically manage these definitions
            through this collection.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SortDefinitions
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The list of SortDefinitions that have been added to the data grid. SortDefinitions are managed by the data
            grid automatically when using the built in filter UI. You can also programmatically manage these definitions
            through this collection.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Virtualize
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If true, the results are displayed in a Virtualize component, allowing a boost in rendering speed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RowClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            CSS class for the table rows. Note, many CSS settings are overridden by MudTd though
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RowStyle
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            CSS styles for the table rows. Note, many CSS settings are overridden by MudTd though
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RowClassFunc
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Returns the class that will get joined with RowClass. Takes the current item and row index.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RowStyleFunc
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Returns the class that will get joined with RowClass. Takes the current item and row index.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: MultiSelection
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Set to true to enable selection of multiple rows.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EditMode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            When the grid is not read only, you can specify what type of editing mode to use.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EditTrigger
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Allows you to specify the action that will trigger an edit when the EditMode is Form.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EditDialogOptions
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fine tune the edit dialog.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Items
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             The data to display in the table. MudTable will render one row per item
             </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Loading
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Show a loading animation, if true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CanCancelEdit
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Define if Cancel button is present or not for inline editing.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: LoadingProgressColor
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The color of the loading progress if used. It supports the theme colors.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ToolBarContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Optional. Add any kind of toolbar to this render fragment.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HorizontalScrollbar
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines if the table has a horizontal scrollbar.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ColumnResizeMode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines if columns of the grid can be resized.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HeaderClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Add a class to the thead tag
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Height
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Setting a height will allow to scroll the table. If not set, it will try to grow in height. You can set this to any CSS value that the
            attribute 'height' accepts, i.e. 500px.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FooterClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Add a class to the tfoot tag
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: QuickFilter
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A function that returns whether or not an item should be displayed in the table. You can use this to implement your own search function.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Header
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Allows adding a custom header beyond that specified in the Column component. Add HeaderCell
            components to add a custom header.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Columns
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The Columns that make up the data grid. Add Column components to this RenderFragment.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ChildRowContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Row Child content of the component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: NoRecordsContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the table body content when there are no matching records found
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: LoadingContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the table body content  the table has no rows and is loading
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: PagerContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Add MudTablePager here to enable breaking the rows in to multiple pages.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ServerData
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Supply an async function which (re)loads filtered, paginated and sorted data from server.
            Table will await this func and update based on the returned TableData.
            Used only with ServerData
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RowsPerPage
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If the table has more items than this number, it will break the rows into pages of said size.
            Note: requires a MudTablePager in PagerContent.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CurrentPage
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The page index of the currently displayed page (Zero based). Usually called by MudTablePager.
            Note: requires a MudTablePager in PagerContent.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ReadOnly
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Locks Inline Edit mode, if true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedItems
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If MultiSelection is true, this returns the currently selected items. You can bind this property and the initial content of the HashSet you bind it to will cause these rows to be selected initially.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedItem
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Returns the item which was last clicked on in single selection mode (that is, if MultiSelection is false)

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ValidationDelay
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Validation debounce delay in milliseconds. This can help improve rendering performance of forms with real-time validation of inputs
            i.e. when textfields have Immediate="true".
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SuppressRenderingOnValidation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            When true, the form will not re-render its child contents on validation updates (i.e. when IsValid changes).
            This is an optimization which can be necessary especially for larger forms on older devices.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SuppressImplicitSubmission
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            When true, will not cause a page refresh on Enter if any input has focus.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            https://www.w3.org/TR/2018/SPSD-html5-20180327/forms.html#implicit-submission
            Usually this is not wanted, as it can cause a page refresh in the middle of editing a form. 
            When the form is in a dialog this will cause the dialog to close. So by default we suppress it.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: Validation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A default validation func or a validation attribute to use for form controls that don't have one.
            Supported types are:
            <para>Func<T, bool> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false</para>
            <para>Func<T, string> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null </para>
            <para>Func<T, IEnumerable< string >> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<object, string, IEnumerable< string >> input Form.Model, Full Path of Member ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task< bool >> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task< string >> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task<IEnumerable< string >>> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<object, string, Task<IEnumerable< string >>> input Form.Model, Full Path of Member ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations.ValidationAttribute instances</para>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: TextUpdateSuppression
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            When TextUpdateSuppression is true (which is default) the text can not be updated by bindings while the component is focused in BSS (not WASM).
            This solves issue #1012: Textfield swallowing chars when typing rapidly
            If you need to update the input's text while it is focused you can set this parameter to false.
            Note: on WASM text update suppression is not active, so this parameter has no effect.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A validation func or a validation attribute. Supported types are:
            <para>Func<T, bool> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false</para>
            <para>Func<T, string> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null </para>
            <para>Func<T, IEnumerable< string >> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<object, string, IEnumerable< string >> input Form.Model, Full Path of Member ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task< bool >> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task< string >> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task<IEnumerable< string >>> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<object, string, Task<IEnumerable< string >>> input Form.Model, Full Path of Member ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations.ValidationAttribute instances</para>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: TextUpdateSuppression
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            When TextUpdateSuppression is true (which is default) the text can not be updated by bindings while the component is focused in BSS (not WASM).
            This solves issue #1012: Textfield swallowing chars when typing rapidly
            If you need to update the input's text while it is focused you can set this parameter to false.
            Note: on WASM text update suppression is not active, so this parameter has no effect.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Validation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A validation func or a validation attribute. Supported types are:
            <para>Func<T, bool> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false</para>
            <para>Func<T, string> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null </para>
            <para>Func<T, IEnumerable< string >> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<object, string, IEnumerable< string >> input Form.Model, Full Path of Member ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task< bool >> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task< string >> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task<IEnumerable< string >>> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<object, string, Task<IEnumerable< string >>> input Form.Model, Full Path of Member ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations.ValidationAttribute instances</para>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Validation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A validation func or a validation attribute. Supported types are:
            <para>Func<T, bool> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false</para>
            <para>Func<T, string> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null </para>
            <para>Func<T, IEnumerable< string >> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<object, string, IEnumerable< string >> input Form.Model, Full Path of Member ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task< bool >> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task< string >> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task<IEnumerable< string >>> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<object, string, Task<IEnumerable< string >>> input Form.Model, Full Path of Member ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations.ValidationAttribute instances</para>
            </summary>

<summary>
            A validation func or a validation attribute. Supported types are:
            <para>Func<T, bool> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false</para>
            <para>Func<T, string> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null </para>
            <para>Func<T, IEnumerable< string >> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<object, string, IEnumerable< string >> input Form.Model, Full Path of Member ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task< bool >> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task< string >> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task<IEnumerable< string >>> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<object, string, Task<IEnumerable< string >>> input Form.Model, Full Path of Member ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations.ValidationAttribute instances</para>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Validation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A validation func or a validation attribute. Supported types are:
            <para>Func<T, bool> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false</para>
            <para>Func<T, string> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null </para>
            <para>Func<T, IEnumerable< string >> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<object, string, IEnumerable< string >> input Form.Model, Full Path of Member ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task< bool >> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task< string >> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task<IEnumerable< string >>> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<object, string, Task<IEnumerable< string >>> input Form.Model, Full Path of Member ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations.ValidationAttribute instances</para>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedItems
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If MultiSelection is true, this returns the currently selected items. You can bind this property and the initial content of the HashSet you bind it to will cause these rows to be selected initially.

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ServerData
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Supply an async function which (re)loads filtered, paginated and sorted data from server.
            Table will await this func and update based on the returned TableData.
            Used only with ServerData
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsEditRowSwitchingBlocked
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            When editing a row and this is true, the editing row must be saved/cancelled before a new row will be selected.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Elevation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The higher the number, the heavier the drop-shadow. 0 for no shadow.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Square
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Set true to disable rounded corners
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Outlined
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If true, table will be outlined.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Bordered
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If true, table's cells will have left/right borders.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Dense
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Set true for rows with a narrow height
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Hover
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Set true to see rows hover on mouse-over.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Striped
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If true, striped table rows will be used.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Breakpoint
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            At what breakpoint the table should switch to mobile layout. Takes None, Xs, Sm, Md, Lg and Xl the default behavior is breaking on Xs.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FixedHeader
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            When true, the header will stay in place when the table is scrolled. Note: set Height to make the table scrollable.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FixedFooter
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            When true, the footer will be visible is not scrolled to the bottom. Note: set Height to make the table scrollable.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Height
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Setting a height will allow to scroll the table. If not set, it will try to grow in height. You can set this to any CSS value that the
            attribute 'height' accepts, i.e. 500px. 
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SortLabel
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If table is in smalldevice mode and uses any kind of sorting the text applied here will be the sort selects label.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AllowUnsorted
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If true allows table to be in an unsorted state through column clicks (i.e. first click sorts "Ascending", second "Descending", third "None").
            If false only "Ascending" and "Descending" states are allowed (i.e. there always should be a column to sort).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RowsPerPage
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If the table has more items than this number, it will break the rows into pages of said size.
            Note: requires a MudTablePager in PagerContent.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RowsPerPageChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Rows Per Page two-way bindable parameter
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CurrentPage
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The page index of the currently displayed page (Zero based). Usually called by MudTablePager.
            Note: requires a MudTablePager in PagerContent.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: MultiSelection
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Set to true to enable selection of multiple rows with check boxes. 
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ToolBarContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Optional. Add any kind of toolbar to this render fragment.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Loading
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Show a loading animation, if true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: LoadingProgressColor
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The color of the loading progress if used. It supports the theme colors.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HeaderContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Add MudTh cells here to define the table header. If <see cref="P:MudBlazor.MudTableBase.CustomHeader" /> is set, add one or more MudTHeadRow instead.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CustomHeader
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specify if the header has multiple rows. In that case, you need to provide the MudTHeadRow tags.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FooterContent

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CustomFooter
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specify if the footer has multiple rows. In that case, you need to provide the MudTFootRow tags.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FooterClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Add a class to the tfoot tag
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ColGroup
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a group of one or more columns in a table for formatting.
            Ex:
            table
                colgroup
                   col span="2" style="background-color:red"
                   col style="background-color:yellow"
                 colgroup
                 header
                 body
            table
            </summary>

<summary>
            Add MudTablePager here to enable breaking the rows in to multiple pages.

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a value that determines if the cached result is to be varied by request culture.
            <para>
            Setting this to <c>true</c> would result in the result to be varied by <see cref="P:System.Globalization.CultureInfo.CurrentCulture" />
            and <see cref="P:System.Globalization.CultureInfo.CurrentUICulture" />.

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:

BoundAttributes.Name: expires-after
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: expires-sliding
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            </summary>

TagHelpers.Name: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.EnvironmentTagHelper
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" /> implementation targeting <environment> elements that conditionally renders
            content based on the current value of <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Hosting.IHostingEnvironment.EnvironmentName" />.
            If the environment is not listed in the specified <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.EnvironmentTagHelper.Names" /> or <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.EnvironmentTagHelper.Include" />,
            or if it is in <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.EnvironmentTagHelper.Exclude" />, the content will not be rendered.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: names
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A comma separated list of environment names in which the content should be rendered.
            If the current environment is also in the <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.EnvironmentTagHelper.Exclude" /> list, the content will not be rendered.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            The specified environment names are compared case insensitively to the current value of
            <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Hosting.IHostingEnvironment.EnvironmentName" />.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: include
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A comma separated list of environment names in which the content should be rendered.
            If the current environment is also in the <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.EnvironmentTagHelper.Exclude" /> list, the content will not be rendered.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            The specified environment names are compared case insensitively to the current value of
            <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Hosting.IHostingEnvironment.EnvironmentName" />.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: exclude
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A comma separated list of environment names in which the content will not be rendered.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            The specified environment names are compared case insensitively to the current value of
            <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Hosting.IHostingEnvironment.EnvironmentName" />.
            </remarks>

TagHelpers.Documentation:

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-for
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            An expression to be evaluated against the current model.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-format
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The format string (see https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/txafckwd.aspx) used to format the
            <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.InputTagHelper.For" /> result. Sets the generated "value" attribute to that formatted string.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            Not used if the provided (see <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.InputTagHelper.InputTypeName" />) or calculated "type" attribute value is
            <c>checkbox</c>, <c>password</c>, or <c>radio</c>. That is, <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.InputTagHelper.Format" /> is used when calling
            <see cref="M:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.ViewFeatures.IHtmlGenerator.GenerateTextBox(Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Rendering.ViewContext,Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.ViewFeatures.ModelExplorer,System.String,System.Object,System.String,System.Object)" />.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: type
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The type of the <input> element.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            Passed through to the generated HTML in all cases. Also used to determine the <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.ViewFeatures.IHtmlGenerator" />
            helper to call and the default <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.InputTagHelper.Format" /> value. A default <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.InputTagHelper.Format" /> is not calculated
            if the provided (see <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.InputTagHelper.InputTypeName" />) or calculated "type" attribute value is <c>checkbox</c>,
            <c>hidden</c>, <c>password</c>, or <c>radio</c>.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: name
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The name of the <input> element.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            Passed through to the generated HTML in all cases. Also used to determine whether <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.InputTagHelper.For" /> is
            valid with an empty <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.ViewFeatures.ModelExpression.Name" />.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: value
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The value of the <input> element.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            Passed through to the generated HTML in all cases. Also used to determine the generated "checked" attribute
            if <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.InputTagHelper.InputTypeName" /> is "radio". Must not be <c>null</c> in that case.
            </remarks>

TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" /> implementation targeting <link> elements that supports fallback href paths.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            The tag helper won't process for cases with just the 'href' attribute.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: href
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Address of the linked resource.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            Passed through to the generated HTML in all cases.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-href-include
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A comma separated list of globbed file patterns of CSS stylesheets to load.
            The glob patterns are assessed relative to the application's 'webroot' setting.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-href-exclude
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A comma separated list of globbed file patterns of CSS stylesheets to exclude from loading.
            The glob patterns are assessed relative to the application's 'webroot' setting.
            Must be used in conjunction with <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.LinkTagHelper.HrefInclude" />.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-fallback-href
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The URL of a CSS stylesheet to fallback to in the case the primary one fails.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-suppress-fallback-integrity
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Boolean value that determines if an integrity hash will be compared with <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.LinkTagHelper.FallbackHref" /> value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-append-version
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Value indicating if file version should be appended to the href urls.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            If <c>true</c> then a query string "v" with the encoded content of the file is added.
            </remarks>

<summary>

            one fails.
            The glob patterns are assessed relative to the application's 'webroot' setting.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-fallback-href-exclude

            the case the primary one fails.
            The glob patterns are assessed relative to the application's 'webroot' setting.
            Must be used in conjunction with <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.LinkTagHelper.FallbackHrefInclude" />.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-fallback-test-class
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            Must be used in conjunction with <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.LinkTagHelper.FallbackTestProperty" /> and <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.LinkTagHelper.FallbackTestValue" />,
            and either <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.LinkTagHelper.FallbackHref" /> or <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.LinkTagHelper.FallbackHrefInclude" />.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-fallback-test-property

            and either <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.LinkTagHelper.FallbackHref" /> or <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.LinkTagHelper.FallbackHrefInclude" />.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-fallback-test-value

            and either <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.LinkTagHelper.FallbackHref" /> or <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.LinkTagHelper.FallbackHrefInclude" />.
            </summary>

TagHelpers.Name: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.OptionTagHelper
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" /> implementation targeting <option> elements.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            This <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" /> works in conjunction with <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.SelectTagHelper" />. It reads elements
            content but does not modify that content. The only modification it makes is to add a <c>selected</c> attribute
            in some cases.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: value
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a value for the <option> element.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            Passed through to the generated HTML in all cases.
            </remarks>

TagHelpers.Name: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.PartialTagHelper
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            Renders a partial view.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: name
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The name or path of the partial view that is rendered to the response.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: for
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            An expression to be evaluated against the current model. Cannot be used together with <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.PartialTagHelper.Model" />.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: model
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The model to pass into the partial view. Cannot be used together with <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.PartialTagHelper.For" />.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: optional
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            When optional, executing the tag helper will no-op if the view cannot be located.
            Otherwise will throw stating the view could not be found.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: fallback-name
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            View to lookup if the view specified by <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.PartialTagHelper.Name" /> cannot be located.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: view-data
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.ViewFeatures.ViewDataDictionary" /> to pass into the partial view.
            </summary>

TagHelpers.Name: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.PersistComponentStateTagHelper
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: persist-mode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:

TagHelpers.Name: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.ScriptTagHelper
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" /> implementation targeting <script> elements that supports fallback src paths.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            The tag helper won't process for cases with just the 'src' attribute.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: src
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Address of the external script to use.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            Passed through to the generated HTML in all cases.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-src-include
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A comma separated list of globbed file patterns of JavaScript scripts to load.
            The glob patterns are assessed relative to the application's 'webroot' setting.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-src-exclude
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A comma separated list of globbed file patterns of JavaScript scripts to exclude from loading.
            The glob patterns are assessed relative to the application's 'webroot' setting.
            Must be used in conjunction with <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.ScriptTagHelper.SrcInclude" />.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-fallback-src
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The URL of a Script tag to fallback to in the case the primary one fails.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-suppress-fallback-integrity
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Boolean value that determines if an integrity hash will be compared with <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.ScriptTagHelper.FallbackSrc" /> value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-append-version
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Value indicating if file version should be appended to src urls.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            A query string "v" with the encoded content of the file is added.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-fallback-src-include
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A comma separated list of globbed file patterns of JavaScript scripts to fallback to in the case the
            primary one fails.
            The glob patterns are assessed relative to the application's 'webroot' setting.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-fallback-src-exclude
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A comma separated list of globbed file patterns of JavaScript scripts to exclude from the fallback list, in
            the case the primary one fails.
            The glob patterns are assessed relative to the application's 'webroot' setting.

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-fallback-test
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            </summary>

            </summary>

            attribute.

TagHelpers.Name: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.ValidationSummaryTagHelper

            attribute.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-validation-summary
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If <see cref="F:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Rendering.ValidationSummary.All" /> or <see cref="F:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Rendering.ValidationSummary.ModelOnly" />, appends a validation
            summary. Otherwise (<see cref="F:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Rendering.ValidationSummary.None" />, the default), this tag helper does nothing.
            </summary>
            <exception cref="T:System.ArgumentException">
            Thrown if setter is called with an undefined <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.ValidationSummaryTagHelper.ValidationSummary" /> value e.g.
            <c>(ValidationSummary)23</c>.
            </exception>

TagHelpers.Name: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Razor.TagHelpers.UrlResolutionTagHelper
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" /> implementation targeting elements containing attributes with URL expected values.
            </summary>
            <remarks>Resolves URLs starting with '~/' (relative to the application's 'webroot' setting) that are not
            targeted by other <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" />s. Runs prior to other <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" />s to ensure
            application-relative URLs are resolved.</remarks>

TagHelpers.Name: Bind
TagHelpers.Documentation: Binds the provided expression to an attribute and a change event, based on the naming of the bind attribute. For example: @bind-value="..." and @bind-value:event="onchange" will assign the current value of the expression to the 'value' attribute, and assign a delegate that attempts to set the value to the 'onchange' attribute.

BoundAttributes.Name: @bind-...
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Binds the provided expression to an attribute and a change event, based on the naming of the bind attribute. For example: @bind-value="..." and @bind-value:event="onchange" will assign the current value of the expression to the 'value' attribute, and assign a delegate that attempts to set the value to the 'onchange' attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: format
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies a format to convert the value specified by the corresponding bind attribute. For example: @bind-value:format="..." will apply a format string to the value specified in @bind-value="...". The format string can currently only be used with expressions of type DateTime.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: event
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the event handler name to attach for change notifications for the value provided by the '@bind-...' attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: culture
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the culture to use for conversions.
